flowRoot.flowPara: All the queries specify a cellId and a time range. This organisation of the data allow fast request on a huge Dynamo database. The nodeID is concatenated to the timestamp to garantee the "unique" primary key
New packets from the WSN gateways arrive at a load balancer
This load balancer dispatch the incoming connections among the instances
According to the charge of the instances, the number of instances is ajusted (Auto scaling)
After processing, the data are stored in a Dynamo DataBase
The frontend push their requests in a queue.
Instances pull thoses request from the queue according to their charge
They parse the request, then retrieve the data from the database. If required, the data are processed.
The instance build the answer and push it in Amazon S3 before to send the link to the frontend trough an another queue.
